{{Spanish name|Balbuena|González}} {{Infobox football biography |name = Fabián Balbuena |image = |caption = |fullname = Fabián Cornelio Balbuena González<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/844127 |title=2018/19 Premier League squads confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=3 September 2018 |accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref> |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|8|23|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Ciudad del Este]], Paraguay |height = 1.88 m<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fichajes.com/jugador/j225552_fabian-cornelio-balbuena-gonzalez|title=Fabián Cornelio Balbuena González - Fichajes.com|website=Fichajes .com: Noticias y rumores sobre el mercado de fichajes de fútbol|accessdate=8 July 2018}}</ref> |position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]] |currentclub = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] |clubnumber = 4 |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = [[Club Cerro Porteño (Presidente Franco)|Cerro Porteño PF]] |years1 = 2010–2012 |clubs1 = [[Club Cerro Porteño (Presidente Franco)|Cerro Porteño PF]] |caps1 = 76 |goals1 = 5 |years2 = 2013 |clubs2 = [[Club Rubio Ñu|Rubio Ñu]] |caps2 = 17 |goals2 = 1 |years3 = 2013–2014 |clubs3 = [[Club Nacional|Nacional]] |caps3 = 30 |goals3 = 1 |years4 = 2014–2016 |clubs4 = [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] |caps4 = 43 |goals4 = 3 |years5 = 2016–2018 |clubs5 = [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] |caps5 = 69 |goals5 = 4 |years6 = 2018– |clubs6 = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] |caps6 = 17 |goals6 = 1 |nationalyears1 = 2015– |nationalteam1 = [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] |nationalcaps1 = 8 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |club-update = 18:29, 22 December 2018 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 21 November 2018 }} '''Fabián Cornelio Balbuena González''' (born 23 August 1991) is a Paraguayan international [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre back]] for English {{English football updater|WestHamU}} club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].
==Club career== ===Paraguay=== Born in [[Ciudad del Este]], Balbuena was promoted to [[Club Cerro Porteño (Presidente Franco)|Cerro Porteño PF]]'s first team in 2010, after the arrival of new manager [[Eduardo Rivera]]. He immediately became a starter under Rivera, playing in all the remaining seven matches of the campaign as his side achieved a mid-table position.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.com.br/noticia/713949_pai-queria-que-balbuena-estudasse-mas-ele-virou-jogador-capitao-aos-20-e-hoje-brilha-no-corinthians|title=Pai queria que Balbuena estudasse, mas ele virou jogador, capitão aos 20 e hoje brilha no Corinthians|trans-title=Balbuena's father wanted him to study, but he became a player, captain at 20 and today shines at Corinthians|publisher=[[ESPN Brasil]]|language=pt|date=28 July 2017|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref>
Balbuena quickly became a regular starter in 2011, being also [[Captain (association football)|team captain]] as the club achieved promotion from [[Paraguayan División Intermedia|División intermedia]]. He scored his first goal for the club on 3 April of that year, netting the game's only in a home success over [[Deportivo Caaguazú]].
Balbuena joined [[Club Rubio Ñu|Rubio Ñu]] ahead of the [[2013 Paraguayan Primera División season|2013 season]], but remained at the club for only six months before moving to defending champions [[Club Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/edicion-impresa/deportes/se-sumo-otro-mazacotte-592820.html|title=Se sumó otro Mazacotte|trans-title=Another Mazacotte joined|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=7 June 2013|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> At the latter side, he was also first-choice and reached the [[2014 Copa Libertadores Finals]], losing it to [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]].
On 15 August 2014, [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] bought 50% of Balbuena's federative rights, and the player signed a four-year deal with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/balbuena-ya-es-gumarelo-1276518.html|title=Balbuena ya es gumarelo|trans-title=Balbuena already is ''gumarelo''|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=15 August 2014|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> Again a mainstay, he won the [[2014 Paraguayan Primera División season|2014 Clausura]] tournament.
===Corinthians=== On 16 February 2016, Balbuena moved abroad for the first time in his career after agreeing to a three-year deal with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] side [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corinthians.com.br/balbuena-assina-com-corinthians-por-tres-temporadas/|title=Balbuena assina com Corinthians por três temporadas|trans-title=Balbuena signs with Corinthians for three seasons|publisher=SC Corinthians Paulista|language=pt|date=16 February 2016|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He made his debut for the club nine days later by starting in a 1–1 [[Campeonato Paulista]] away draw against [[Esporte Clube São Bento|São Bento]], and scored his first goal on 19 March in a 4–0 home routing of [[Clube Atlético Linense|Linense]] for the same competition.
A key defensive unit at ''Timão'', Balbuena lifted the [[2017 Campeonato Paulista]], [[2017 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] and [[2018 Campeonato Paulista]] during his spell. On 24 April 2018, he signed a new four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corinthians.com.br/fabian-balbuena-renova-contrato-por-quatro-temporadas/|title=Fabián Balbuena renova contrato por quatro temporadas|trans-title=Fabián Balbuena renews contract for four seasons|publisher=SC Corinthians Paulista|language=pt|date=24 April 2018|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref>
===West Ham United=== On 14 July 2018, Balbuena signed for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on a three-year deal, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/july/14-july/west-ham-sign-paraguay-defender-balbuena|title=West Ham sign Paraguay defender Balbuena|publisher=West Ham United FC|date=14 July 2018|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 12 August in a 4–0 defeat by [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45073328|title=Salah, Mane & Sturridge on target as Liverpool beat West Ham 4–0|date=12 August 2018|accessdate=13 August 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 27 October he scored his first goal for the Hammers to open the scoring at [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], but deflected [[Wilfred Ndidi]]'s long-range shot into his own net for the equaliser; he was the first Paraguayan to score in England's top division since [[Antolín Alcaraz]] in May 2012.<ref>{{cite news |title=Leicester City 1&ndash;1 West Ham United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45924072 |accessdate=28 October 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 October 2018}}</ref>
==International career== First called up on 19 March 2015, Balbuena made his full international debut for [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]] on 31 March by starting in a 1–0 [[Exhibition match|friendly]] loss against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] at the [[Arrowhead Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2015/3/31/8323799/mexico-paraguay-2015-final-score-result|title=Mexico vs. Paraguay 2015: Final score 1–0, El Tri run rampant in Kansas City|publisher=[[SB Nation]]|date=31 March 2015|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He was also named among the 23-man squads for the [[2015 Copa América]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/los-23-elegidos-1371359.html|title=Los 23 elegidos de Díaz|trans-title=Díaz's 23 chosen ones|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=28 May 2015|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> and the [[Copa América Centenario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/edicion-impresa/deportes/solo-un-par-de-nuevos-entre-los-de-siempre-1478624.html|title=Solo un par de nuevos entre los de siempre|trans-title=Only a bunch of newbies among the usual ones|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=10 May 2016|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He made his first competitive appearance at the latter in the final group game, a 1–0 loss to hosts the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in which he was substituted at half time for attacker [[Juan Iturbe]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Shorthanded USA outlasts Paraguay 1&ndash;0 to advance to 2016 Copa America quarterfinals |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/06/12/01/48/160611-mnt-shorthanded-defeats-paraguay-1-0-to-adavnce-to-copa-america-quarterfinals |accessdate=28 October 2018 |publisher=U.S. Soccer |date=11 June 2016}}</ref>
